11
00:01:41.098 --> 00:01:42.431
Aah!

12
00:03:01.317 --> 00:03:03.031
Couldn't sleep?

13
00:03:04.586 --> 00:03:05.986
No.

14
00:03:07.052 --> 00:03:09.586
Me. either.

15
00:03:09.619 --> 00:03:11.752
Is your room okay?

16
00:03:11.786 --> 00:03:14.252
I'm going to find a way to pay you back.

17
00:03:14.286 --> 00:03:16.552
Don't worry about it.

18
00:03:23.219 --> 00:03:24.752
Feel like a drive?

19
00:03:24.786 --> 00:03:26.286
Where to?

20
00:03:29.752 --> 00:03:31.786
Suspicious. aren't you?

21
00:04:15.086 --> 00:04:16.519
I drove it on the way in.

22
00:04:17.819 --> 00:04:20.152
Wow.

23
00:04:20.186 --> 00:04:22.786
Yeah. you don't get sunrises
like this back in Manhattan.

24
00:04:24.252 --> 00:04:25.519
No.

25
00:05:26.086 --> 00:05:28.152
Not really a sunrise diner. is it?

26
00:05:28.186 --> 00:05:29.719
I guess not.

27
00:05:32.219 --> 00:05:33.752
So I do have one question for you.

28
00:05:33.786 --> 00:05:36.186
What's that?

29
00:05:36.219 --> 00:05:38.686
Is there a Mr. Trudy?

30
00:05:39.919 --> 00:05:40.886
There's a Frank.

31
00:05:40.919 --> 00:05:41.952
Is he your husband?

32
00:05:41.986 --> 00:05:43.786
That's two questions.

33
00:05:45.319 --> 00:05:47.952
My turn.

34
00:05:47.986 --> 00:05:49.619
What's a guy like you
doing driving a truck?

35
00:05:49.652 --> 00:05:51.119
Ask me something else.

36
00:05:55.719 --> 00:05:57.952
I'm just folksinging my father's footsteps.

37
00:05:59.286 --> 00:06:01.119
What would you like to do?

38
00:06:01.152 --> 00:06:02.719
That's two questions.

39
00:06:05.986 --> 00:06:07.652
What do you mean?

40
00:06:07.686 --> 00:06:10.086
With your life.

41
00:06:10.119 --> 00:06:11.152
If you could do anything.

42
00:06:11.186 --> 00:06:12.819
But I can't.

43
00:06:12.852 --> 00:06:14.952
Come on.

44
00:06:14.986 --> 00:06:16.319
Honestly?

45
00:06:16.352 --> 00:06:17.286
Yeah.

46
00:06:19.886 --> 00:06:21.252
Just about anything else.

47
00:06:29.586 --> 00:06:30.852
Thanks for the sunrise.

48
00:06:30.886 --> 00:06:32.119
Where are you going?

49
00:06:32.152 --> 00:06:34.052
To pay you back.

50
00:06:35.119 --> 00:06:36.519
Wish me luck.

51
00:06:57.019 --> 00:06:58.052
Good morning.

52
00:06:59.119 --> 00:07:00.186
If you want to eat.

53
00:07:00.219 --> 00:07:01.852
you got to pay first.

54
00:07:01.886 --> 00:07:04.186
Sign in the window says
you need a waitress.

55
00:07:06.852 --> 00:07:08.186
You planning on staying here?

56
00:07:08.219 --> 00:07:11.886
I don't know. but I could use a job.

57
00:07:13.019 --> 00:07:14.152
I'll think about it.

58
00:07:15.619 --> 00:07:16.886
What's thereto think about?

59
00:07:16.919 --> 00:07:18.986
You got a job. and I need one.

60
00:07:19.019 --> 00:07:23.019
Announcer on TV: Let's all
play "Guess My Game."

61
00:07:25.152 --> 00:07:27.952
Mr. Blake. a call came in for you.

62
00:07:27.986 --> 00:07:29.019
When?

63
00:07:29.052 --> 00:07:31.286
A few minutes ago.No message.

64
00:07:31.319 --> 00:07:32.886
First the popular columnist
whose "Voice of Broadway"

65
00:07:32.919 --> 00:07:34.919
appears in papers coast to coast:

66
00:07:34.952 --> 00:07:36.819
Miss Dorothy Dixon.

67
00:07:36.852 --> 00:07:38.819
Thank you. ladies and gentlemen.

68
00:07:38.852 --> 00:07:40.786
I normally don't introduce anyone

69
00:07:40.819 --> 00:07:42.952
who's shorter than myself. but--

70
00:07:50.219 --> 00:07:51.986
Can you bring the bacon in. please. Amy?

71
00:07:52.019 --> 00:07:53.186
Yes. Mommy.

72
00:07:54.986 --> 00:07:56.619
Very good. Thank you.

73
00:07:56.652 --> 00:07:58.013
Which way do the knives go. Jenny?

74
00:08:02.919 --> 00:08:05.686
So what shall we do after school today?

75
00:08:06.986 --> 00:08:08.319
Good morning. Mother.

76
00:08:08.352 --> 00:08:09.319
Good morning. Thomas.

77
00:08:09.352 --> 00:08:10.752
Good morning.

78
00:08:10.786 --> 00:08:13.219
- Coffee?
- Thank you.

79
00:08:16.686 --> 00:08:18.586
We all ready for the day ahead?

80
00:08:18.619 --> 00:08:20.220
- Yes. Father.
- Yes. Father.- Yes. Papa.

81
00:08:20.252 --> 00:08:21.819
Then why is your textbook open

82
00:08:21.852 --> 00:08:23.219
at the breakfast table. Thomas?

83
00:08:23.252 --> 00:08:25.986
Um. sorry. Father.

84
00:08:26.019 --> 00:08:26.986
I have a test today.

85
00:08:27.019 --> 00:08:28.919
Did you study last night?

86
00:08:28.952 --> 00:08:29.986
I did.

87
00:08:31.352 --> 00:08:34.186
It's just there's this boy Randolph.

88
00:08:34.219 --> 00:08:36.752
I don't want him to get the high score.

89
00:08:36.786 --> 00:08:38.252
Competition is healthy.

90
00:08:38.286 --> 00:08:40.252
He's just so annoying.

91
00:08:40.286 --> 00:08:43.652
He wears his hair past his collar

92
00:08:43.686 --> 00:08:45.919
and challenges teachers in class.

93
00:08:45.952 --> 00:08:47.552
Nonconformist.

94
00:08:47.586 --> 00:08:48.552
And proud of it.

95
00:08:48.586 --> 00:08:49.719
He makes negative comments

96
00:08:49.752 --> 00:08:50.919
about the school all the time.

97
00:08:50.952 --> 00:08:54.786
Why do you want to succeed. son?

98
00:08:56.586 --> 00:08:58.752
Why do you want to do well in school?

99
00:09:04.952 --> 00:09:06.652
To make my family proud.

100
00:09:07.886 --> 00:09:10.519
To bring honor to my school.

101
00:09:11.619 --> 00:09:12.919
To serve my country.

102
00:09:12.952 --> 00:09:15.719
Your goals are directed outward.

103
00:09:15.752 --> 00:09:18.986
A boy like Randolph

104
00:09:19.019 --> 00:09:21.119
wants only to gratify himself.

105
00:09:21.152 --> 00:09:24.752
This is the path to moral decay.

106
00:09:24.786 --> 00:09:29.019
The decadence ruined this
country before the war.

107
00:09:29.052 --> 00:09:32.819
You will grow to be a
useful member of society.

108
00:09:32.852 --> 00:09:34.952
You will make our nation stronger.

109
00:09:34.986 --> 00:09:36.886
Randolph will not.

110
00:09:36.919 --> 00:09:39.686
whatever his test score.

111
00:09:39.719 --> 00:09:41.952
Your father's a wise man. son.

112
00:09:44.919 --> 00:09:46.786
You may study at the
breakfast table. Thomas.

113
00:09:47.919 --> 00:09:50.152
Just this morning.

114
00:09:50.186 --> 00:09:51.919
Thank you. Father.

115
00:09:53.319 --> 00:09:54.552
Excuse me.

116
00:10:07.252 --> 00:10:08.852
Yes?

117
00:10:08.886 --> 00:10:09.852
You called?

118
00:10:09.886 --> 00:10:11.619
Where were you. Joe?

119
00:10:11.652 --> 00:10:13.986
I. uh. couldn't sleep.

120
00:10:14.019 --> 00:10:15.786
I went for a drive.

121
00:10:15.819 --> 00:10:18.052
Has your contact approached you?

122
00:10:19.852 --> 00:10:20.986
No. not yet.

123
00:10:21.019 --> 00:10:23.219
He must be assessing you.

124
00:10:23.252 --> 00:10:25.952
make sure you're not a Nazi agent.

125
00:10:25.986 --> 00:10:29.719
We received intelligence this morning.

126
00:10:29.752 --> 00:10:33.286
We believe a courier is carrying
some cargo from San Francisco.

127
00:10:33.319 --> 00:10:34.886
Okay. what's his name?

128
00:10:34.919 --> 00:10:38.052
It's a woman. not a man.

129
00:10:38.086 --> 00:10:40.852
Now. we don't know if she's
headed to Canon City.

130
00:10:40.886 --> 00:10:43.052
but you're to report in
immediately if you see her.

131
00:10:49.986 --> 00:10:51.819
Is she carrying a film. too?

132
00:10:54.586 --> 00:10:56.586
Who said you were carrying a film?

133
00:10:56.619 --> 00:10:57.952
I checked the cargo.

134
00:10:57.986 --> 00:10:59.086
I wanted to make sure it was safe.

135
00:10:59.119 --> 00:11:03.052
Joe. those weren’t your orders.

136
00:11:03.086 --> 00:11:06.086
I'm sorry. sir.

137
00:11:06.119 --> 00:11:08.052
But what's so important about a film?

138
00:11:08.086 --> 00:11:10.319
It's not your place to ask questions. Joe.

139
00:11:10.352 --> 00:11:13.552
Satisfy yourself with following orders.

140
00:11:13.586 --> 00:11:14.819
Understand?

141
00:11:16.252 --> 00:11:18.919
Yes. Obergruppenführer.

142
00:11:18.952 --> 00:11:22.252
You're performing a great
service for the Fatherland.

143
00:11:22.286 --> 00:11:23.886
Heil Hitler.

144
00:11:32.019 --> 00:11:35.252
No. No.

145
00:12:14.019 --> 00:12:17.052
Why aren't you circumcised. Mr. Frink?

146
00:12:17.086 --> 00:12:19.052
Why-- Why would I be?

147
00:12:19.086 --> 00:12:20.167
We've examined the records.

148
00:12:20.186 --> 00:12:22.252
Your grandfather Sheldon Frink--

149
00:12:22.286 --> 00:12:23.752
My grandmother was Christian.

150
00:12:23.786 --> 00:12:25.152
So were my mother and father.

151
00:12:25.186 --> 00:12:27.752
Jews don't get to decide if they're Jews.

152
00:12:27.786 --> 00:12:30.852
Not that I care.

153
00:12:30.886 --> 00:12:33.686
There are no Jews in Japan. after all.

154
00:12:33.719 --> 00:12:36.019
But our racial laws are now
aligned with the Reich.

155
00:12:36.052 --> 00:12:40.152
so it's not just you who
should be exterminated

156
00:12:40.186 --> 00:12:43.986
but also your sister Laura
and her children. too.

157
00:12:53.586 --> 00:12:55.052
You can't.

158
00:12:55.086 --> 00:12:56.719
The law is the law.

159
00:12:56.752 --> 00:12:59.719
Please. Please.

160
00:12:59.752 --> 00:13:03.686
I'm-- I'm begging you. please. Please.

161
00:13:07.752 --> 00:13:13.052
I could overlook this
if you cooperate fully.

162
00:13:13.086 --> 00:13:15.186
Yeah. yeah.

163
00:13:15.219 --> 00:13:18.919
All right. I. uh...

164
00:13:18.952 --> 00:13:20.232
What is it? What is it you want?

165
00:13:24.852 --> 00:13:26.319
You know what I want.

166
00:13:26.352 --> 00:13:27.886
The film.

167
00:13:27.919 --> 00:13:30.952
Trudy Walker gave it to your girlfriend.

168
00:13:30.986 --> 00:13:33.019
who has now fled.

169
00:13:33.052 --> 00:13:35.719
Where is Juliana Crain?

170
00:13:56.186 --> 00:13:57.586
Carl. thank you.

171
00:13:57.619 --> 00:13:59.052
- Thank you.
- Have a good day.

172
00:14:07.752 --> 00:14:09.852
Man: Miss?

173
00:14:09.886 --> 00:14:11.586
Miss?

174
00:14:19.219 --> 00:14:21.186
Here you go.

175
00:14:21.219 --> 00:14:23.019
What are you reading?

176
00:14:24.119 --> 00:14:25.586
You don't know what this is?

177
00:14:26.752 --> 00:14:27.786
Should I?

178
00:14:27.819 --> 00:14:28.886
It's a Bible.

179
00:14:28.919 --> 00:14:30.652
I haven't seen one of those

180
00:14:30.686 --> 00:14:32.552
since I was a little girl.

181
00:14:32.586 --> 00:14:33.952
Take a look.

182
00:14:37.286 --> 00:14:39.186
Hmm.

183
00:14:39.219 --> 00:14:40.852
Lighter than I remember.

184
00:14:40.886 --> 00:14:42.319
King James translation.

185
00:14:42.352 --> 00:14:44.286
He preferred small print.

186
00:14:48.852 --> 00:14:50.886
Those are forbidden in the Pacific States.

187
00:14:50.919 --> 00:14:52.186
The Reich. too.

188
00:14:53.586 --> 00:14:55.219
How'd you get it?

189
00:14:55.252 --> 00:14:56.952
You can find a lot of interesting things

190
00:14:56.986 --> 00:14:58.219
in the Neutral Zone.

191
00:14:58.252 --> 00:15:00.219
Don't you think?

192
00:15:36.652 --> 00:15:39.586
Japanese women aren't easily discouraged.

193
00:15:39.619 --> 00:15:41.552
They slam at those steel monsters

194
00:15:41.586 --> 00:15:42.986
as though they were beating
up their husbands.

195
00:15:44.819 --> 00:15:46.686
Do something. do something.
Say. that's a good idea.

196
00:15:46.719 --> 00:15:48.919
Maybe I can do something. Sure. Whoo-hoo!

197
00:15:55.086 --> 00:15:57.986
Man: It was 9:17 AM. Monday
the fourth of October.

198
00:15:58.019 --> 00:16:00.986
Detectives Foreman and Decker
investigating for the Reich police.

199
00:16:01.019 --> 00:16:02.819
4.000 marks had been reported missing

200
00:16:02.852 --> 00:16:05.819
from the payroll at 123
Street Agricultural Trust.

201
00:16:05.852 --> 00:16:07.286
Woman: How can I help you. detective?

202
00:16:07.319 --> 00:16:09.019
I was just getting ready for work.

203
00:16:09.052 --> 00:16:11.652
Man: And do you keep this
drawer locked. ma'am?

204
00:16:11.686 --> 00:16:14.652
Woman: Oh. I see. How silly of me.

205
00:16:14.686 --> 00:16:17.819
A lock's not much good if just
about anyone has access and a key.

206
00:16:17.852 --> 00:16:19.219
Man: Yes. ma'am.

207
00:16:19.252 --> 00:16:20.586
Woman: But who would do such a thing?

208
00:16:20.619 --> 00:16:22.052
Stealing money from the trust.

209
00:16:22.086 --> 00:16:23.052
that's like stealing from the Reich itself.

210
00:16:26.186 --> 00:16:27.786
Man #2: Stay back. you dumb cop!

211
00:16:27.819 --> 00:16:29.986
I'm through with your Reich lies!

212
00:16:31.352 --> 00:16:33.819
I want Foreman here. and I want him now!

213
00:16:33.852 --> 00:16:35.852
Or this dippy dough-head gets it!

214
00:16:46.886 --> 00:16:48.019
We are grateful to you

215
00:16:48.052 --> 00:16:49.686
for agreeing to this meeting.

216
00:16:49.719 --> 00:16:51.686
We want to ensure nothing disrupts

217
00:16:51.719 --> 00:16:53.852
the visit of the crown prince
and princess tomorrow.

218
00:16:53.886 --> 00:16:55.686
I believe everything is in hand.

219
00:16:55.719 --> 00:16:57.219
What is your concern. Ambassador?

220
00:16:59.352 --> 00:17:01.919
We understand you've arrested suspects

221
00:17:01.952 --> 00:17:03.586
smuggling subversive films.

222
00:17:03.619 --> 00:17:07.052
ones produced by the so-called
Man In the High Castle

223
00:17:07.086 --> 00:17:08.286
before his death.

224
00:17:08.319 --> 00:17:09.852
We've heard rumors

225
00:17:09.886 --> 00:17:11.686
the Man In the High Castle is still alive.

226
00:17:11.719 --> 00:17:14.319
No. he's dead. We've known for some months.

227
00:17:14.352 --> 00:17:15.952
We understand a fourth suspect

228
00:17:15.986 --> 00:17:17.152
fled with the films they were smuggling.

229
00:17:17.186 --> 00:17:18.619
A woman.

230
00:17:18.652 --> 00:17:21.086
You seem very well informed.

231
00:17:21.119 --> 00:17:22.952
Oberführer Diels.

232
00:17:22.986 --> 00:17:24.852
What else do you wish to know?

233
00:17:24.886 --> 00:17:27.919
Uh. we assume she fled to the Neutral Zone.

234
00:17:27.952 --> 00:17:29.919
We need to know where precisely.

235
00:17:29.952 --> 00:17:32.552
We are making inquiries.

236
00:17:32.586 --> 00:17:35.319
The Führer has decreed these
films be confiscated.

237
00:17:35.352 --> 00:17:38.286
Let me speak plainly. Tagomi-san.

238
00:17:38.319 --> 00:17:41.052
If you don't find this woman. we will.

239
00:17:44.719 --> 00:17:47.552
Duly acknowledged. Ambassador.

240
00:17:49.852 --> 00:17:54.019
But. respectfully. gentlemen.

241
00:17:54.052 --> 00:17:58.019
please be aware you’re on Japanese soil.

242
00:17:58.052 --> 00:18:03.752
We recognize the sovereignty of
the Pacific States. Minister.

243
00:18:03.786 --> 00:18:06.219
but this is a matter of state security.

244
00:18:06.252 --> 00:18:07.652
Good day. gentlemen.

245
00:18:30.319 --> 00:18:31.886
Check. please.

246
00:18:37.752 --> 00:18:39.119
3 marks.

247
00:18:40.919 --> 00:18:42.719
Here you go.

248
00:18:42.752 --> 00:18:44.919
You know what I was reading just now?

249
00:18:46.752 --> 00:18:48.752
The Book of Ecclesiastes.

250
00:18:48.786 --> 00:18:50.052
Oh. yeah?

251
00:18:50.086 --> 00:18:52.986
It says all life under the sun is futile.

252
00:18:53.019 --> 00:18:54.086
pointless.

253
00:18:54.119 --> 00:18:55.986
so we should dedicate our life

254
00:18:56.019 --> 00:18:57.619
to what's beyond the sun.

255
00:18:59.186 --> 00:19:01.052
Sounds interesting.

256
00:19:01.086 --> 00:19:02.852
What's beyond the sun?

257
00:19:04.686 --> 00:19:07.986
The Japanese say it's the emperor himself.

258
00:19:08.019 --> 00:19:10.719
beyond which there's only
duty to one's country.

259
00:19:10.752 --> 00:19:12.619
Self-sacrifice.

260
00:19:12.652 --> 00:19:14.086
And the Nazis?

261
00:19:15.619 --> 00:19:17.186
They say there's nothing at all.

262
00:19:17.219 --> 00:19:18.719
What do you say?

263
00:19:18.752 --> 00:19:21.719
Chapter 12. verse 5.

264
00:19:26.252 --> 00:19:28.686
You can pick up a copy at the bookstore.

265
00:19:41.052 --> 00:19:42.652
Raeder: You spoke to Joe
Blake this morning.

266
00:19:42.686 --> 00:19:44.152
Smith: I did.

267
00:19:44.186 --> 00:19:46.686
He should have been contacted by now.

268
00:19:46.719 --> 00:19:49.219
Well. it appears his contact is being
cautious.

269
00:19:50.752 --> 00:19:52.586
You don't think they suspect him.

270
00:19:52.619 --> 00:19:53.552
They suspect everyone.

271
00:19:55.586 --> 00:19:57.752
Steady. Erich.

272
00:19:57.786 --> 00:19:59.052
The bigger the fish.

273
00:19:59.086 --> 00:20:01.086
the greater the patience to catch it.

274
00:20:01.119 --> 00:20:02.752
This so-called Man In the High Castle.

275
00:20:02.786 --> 00:20:04.052
Reich Minister Goebbels says

276
00:20:04.086 --> 00:20:06.252
that not even Fraulein Riefenstahl

277
00:20:06.286 --> 00:20:08.019
could make films of such sophistication.

278
00:20:08.052 --> 00:20:09.886
If he made them.

279
00:20:09.919 --> 00:20:11.319
I don't understand.

280
00:20:11.352 --> 00:20:12.919
If he didn't. who did?

281
00:20:18.219 --> 00:20:20.252
I've heard strange rumors.

282
00:20:20.286 --> 00:20:21.752
Rumors?

283
00:20:21.786 --> 00:20:23.586
That the Führer considers the films

284
00:20:23.619 --> 00:20:26.586
a threat to the very
existence of the Reich.

285
00:20:26.619 --> 00:20:28.139
That's why he's so obsessed with them.

286
00:20:29.819 --> 00:20:31.819
Preposterous. isn't it?

287
00:20:31.852 --> 00:20:34.086
The Führer is not inclined
to idle obsession.

288
00:20:38.752 --> 00:20:40.086
Down!

289
00:20:46.319 --> 00:20:47.652
Man: Reload!

290
00:20:47.686 --> 00:20:50.719
Man: Is he dead?

291
00:21:31.352 --> 00:21:35.286
- Over here!
- Circle round! Circle round!

292
00:21:38.052 --> 00:21:38.986
Shit.

293
00:21:41.186 --> 00:21:43.719
Come on. Go!

294
00:22:21.586 --> 00:22:22.819
Hey. Ed.

295
00:22:28.252 --> 00:22:30.252
Mr. Windham-Matson. sir.

296
00:22:30.286 --> 00:22:31.886
Hey. good morning. Ed.
How's your grandfather?

297
00:22:31.919 --> 00:22:33.086
He's fine. sir. thank you.

298
00:22:33.119 --> 00:22:35.286
That should have two more cases on it.

299
00:22:35.319 --> 00:22:36.686
What can I help you with?

300
00:22:36.719 --> 00:22:38.319
It's Frank Frink. sir.

301
00:22:38.352 --> 00:22:39.852
I was wondering if he phoned in sick today.

302
00:22:39.886 --> 00:22:41.752
No. he hasn't.

303
00:22:41.786 --> 00:22:44.586
It's just that his phone doesn't pick up.

304
00:22:44.619 --> 00:22:47.552
Do you mind if I check to see if he's okay?

305
00:22:47.586 --> 00:22:48.952
You can dock my pay. of course.

306
00:22:48.986 --> 00:22:50.319
Go on.

307
00:22:50.352 --> 00:22:52.119
Thank you. sir.

308
00:22:52.152 --> 00:22:53.719
And don't worry.I will!

309
00:23:01.686 --> 00:23:02.486
Frank.

310
00:23:06.352 --> 00:23:09.252
Frank.Is that your name?

311
00:23:12.086 --> 00:23:13.286
Over here.

312
00:23:28.652 --> 00:23:30.052
It's okay. I'm a friend.

313
00:23:30.086 --> 00:23:32.819
I gave that film to Trudy Walker.

314
00:23:32.852 --> 00:23:34.919
Then you're definitely not a friend.

315
00:23:34.952 --> 00:23:38.252
You got to tell them I have
nothing to do with this.

316
00:23:38.286 --> 00:23:39.986
I'd save you if I could.

317
00:23:40.019 --> 00:23:41.652
I can't.

318
00:23:52.986 --> 00:23:54.952
Who the hell are you?

319
00:23:54.986 --> 00:23:57.186
A man. just like you.

320
00:23:57.219 --> 00:23:58.886
A man who wants to breathe free.

321
00:23:58.919 --> 00:24:01.886
Spare me the propaganda
bullshit. all right?

322
00:24:01.919 --> 00:24:03.186
I meant your name.

323
00:24:06.319 --> 00:24:07.652
Randall.

324
00:24:07.686 --> 00:24:08.952
Well. Randall.

325
00:24:08.986 --> 00:24:10.186
I don't want your type of freedom.

326
00:24:10.219 --> 00:24:11.852
I don't want anything.

327
00:24:13.119 --> 00:24:17.686
It takes a lot of effort not to be free--

328
00:24:17.719 --> 00:24:20.219
keeping your head down.
holding your tongue.

329
00:24:20.252 --> 00:24:23.986
I'm all for keeping my head
down and my mouth shut.

330
00:24:24.019 --> 00:24:25.986
as long as I get to live.

331
00:24:26.019 --> 00:24:28.719
There's things worth more than
your life. and you know it.

332
00:24:33.652 --> 00:24:35.552
You know where Trudy's sister went.

333
00:24:40.286 --> 00:24:42.619
Don't you?

334
00:24:42.652 --> 00:24:44.852
What do you know about that?

335
00:24:44.886 --> 00:24:46.952
The question is what do you know?

336
00:24:51.986 --> 00:24:55.052
Yeah. you know where she went.

337
00:24:55.086 --> 00:24:56.919
Why don't you tell them?

338
00:25:00.719 --> 00:25:02.852
They'll kill me anyway.

339
00:25:02.886 --> 00:25:03.886
Maybe.

340
00:25:05.352 --> 00:25:08.752
Why don't you tell them
and see what happens?

341
00:25:08.786 --> 00:25:11.819
If you can believe they'll keep their word.

342
00:25:18.019 --> 00:25:19.752
Hey. can I take a break?

343
00:25:22.152 --> 00:25:24.286
- Ten minutes.
- Thank you.

344
00:25:24.319 --> 00:25:25.286
Mm-hmm.

345
00:25:46.719 --> 00:25:49.752
♪ ...maybe so

346
00:25:49.786 --> 00:25:55.286
♪ But in my heart I know

347
00:25:55.319 --> 00:26:00.552
♪ I'll never get old

348
00:26:06.619 --> 00:26:08.086
Hello.

349
00:26:08.119 --> 00:26:09.786
Hello.

350
00:26:13.619 --> 00:26:16.019
I'm. uh. I'm looking for a Bible.

351
00:26:18.619 --> 00:26:19.952
A Bible?

352
00:26:19.986 --> 00:26:23.286
Old Testament. please.

353
00:26:23.319 --> 00:26:25.119
King James translation.

354
00:26:27.752 --> 00:26:30.019
What makes you think I have one of those?

355
00:26:30.052 --> 00:26:31.852
Someone told me you did.

356
00:26:36.252 --> 00:26:37.752
It's not like they're illegal or anything.

357
00:26:37.786 --> 00:26:39.519
Right?

358
00:26:42.086 --> 00:26:44.086
No laws around here.

359
00:26:45.286 --> 00:26:48.219
They may not be illegal. but. uh.

360
00:26:48.252 --> 00:26:50.619
that doesn't exactly make them legal.

361
00:26:50.652 --> 00:26:53.086
if you know what I mean.

362
00:26:53.119 --> 00:26:54.986
Of course.

363
00:26:59.352 --> 00:27:01.019
Do you have one?

364
00:27:03.252 --> 00:27:04.552
Please?

365
00:27:21.952 --> 00:27:23.052
7 marks.

366
00:27:37.752 --> 00:27:38.852
Thank you.

367
00:27:49.052 --> 00:27:51.252
Man: Go. go. go!

368
00:27:51.286 --> 00:27:53.219
Are you all right. Obergruppenführer?

369
00:27:53.252 --> 00:27:54.919
- How's Erich?
- He's in critical condition.

370
00:27:54.952 --> 00:27:57.286
One of the bullets lodged
only 2 inches from his heart.

371
00:27:57.319 --> 00:27:58.819
I'm afraid I have more bad news. sir.

372
00:27:58.852 --> 00:28:00.086
Don't be coy. Lawrence.

373
00:28:00.119 --> 00:28:01.619
It's Hauptaturmführer Lautz.

374
00:28:01.652 --> 00:28:02.686
His vehicle's gone missing.

375
00:28:02.719 --> 00:28:04.086
Missing when?

376
00:28:04.119 --> 00:28:05.920
Last seen crossing the
Pelham Bridge at 8:41.

377
00:28:05.952 --> 00:28:07.152
No sign of him or his driver since.

378
00:28:07.186 --> 00:28:08.852
These were coordinated attacks.

379
00:28:08.886 --> 00:28:11.052
reprisals for the Resistance
leader we killed.

380
00:28:11.086 --> 00:28:12.919
What about the man I apprehended?

381
00:28:12.952 --> 00:28:14.986
A Semite. sir. known as Doc.

382
00:28:15.019 --> 00:28:16.119
Born Jason Meyer.

383
00:28:16.152 --> 00:28:18.086
Parents exterminated Cincinnati Camp.

384
00:28:18.119 --> 00:28:20.052
May 17. 1951.

385
00:28:20.086 --> 00:28:21.286
We wipe them out.

386
00:28:21.319 --> 00:28:22.952
yet they keep coming back like lice.

387
00:28:22.986 --> 00:28:25.752
Lice don't assassinate Nazi officers.

388
00:28:25.786 --> 00:28:26.852
I only meant--

389
00:28:26.886 --> 00:28:28.186
It may reassure you

390
00:28:28.219 --> 00:28:30.619
to liken terrorists to insects.

391
00:28:30.652 --> 00:28:32.986
but they inflicted great
damage on us today.

392
00:28:33.019 --> 00:28:34.319
Never underestimate them.

393
00:28:34.352 --> 00:28:36.119
Yes. Obergruppenführer.

394
00:28:36.152 --> 00:28:38.886
I vary my route every day.

395
00:28:38.919 --> 00:28:42.119
and yet this Semite knew
exactly where to find us.

396
00:28:42.152 --> 00:28:44.152
- How could he. sir?
- I don't know.

397
00:28:46.152 --> 00:28:47.986
But I intend to find out.

398
00:29:05.319 --> 00:29:06.786
Frank. you in there?

399
00:29:14.686 --> 00:29:16.852
Oh. Jesus.

400
00:29:21.852 --> 00:29:23.119
Fuck!

401
00:29:23.152 --> 00:29:26.219
What are you doing? Frank!

402
00:29:26.252 --> 00:29:27.852
Even if you broke the chains.

403
00:29:27.886 --> 00:29:29.619
how do you think you're
going to get out of here?

404
00:29:29.652 --> 00:29:31.952
Fuck!

405
00:29:38.719 --> 00:29:40.286
Was it worth it?

406
00:29:40.319 --> 00:29:44.586
All so you could pass on
that stupid film of yours.

407
00:29:44.619 --> 00:29:46.852
That film can change the world.

408
00:29:46.886 --> 00:29:49.119
Yeah. it certainly changed mine.

409
00:29:49.152 --> 00:29:51.319
Why do you think they torture us?

410
00:29:51.352 --> 00:29:53.319
I got a feeling you're going to tell me.

411
00:29:53.352 --> 00:29:55.686
Because they know that
that film shows the world

412
00:29:55.719 --> 00:29:58.619
not as it is but as it could be.

413
00:29:58.652 --> 00:30:00.052
Yeah. well. in this world.

414
00:30:00.086 --> 00:30:01.186
they flattened D.C.with an A bomb.

415
00:30:01.219 --> 00:30:02.252
How do you people think a film

416
00:30:02.286 --> 00:30:03.619
is going to fight against that?

417
00:30:03.652 --> 00:30:05.652
- "You people"?
- Yeah. you people.

418
00:30:05.686 --> 00:30:07.119
You dead-enders in the Resistance.

419
00:30:07.152 --> 00:30:08.886
How many are you anyway. huh?

420
00:30:08.919 --> 00:30:10.852
What. like seven. ten. 12?

421
00:30:10.886 --> 00:30:13.886
You really think you're going
to defeat the Japanese?

422
00:30:13.919 --> 00:30:15.986
The Nazis?

423
00:30:16.019 --> 00:30:17.786
Of course.

424
00:30:17.819 --> 00:30:19.719
That's not the way it looks from here!

425
00:30:28.752 --> 00:30:31.286
Evil triumphs only when
good men do nothing.

426
00:30:35.152 --> 00:30:36.986
- Hi.
- Hello.

427
00:30:46.786 --> 00:30:47.886
Can I help you find something?

428
00:30:47.919 --> 00:30:49.519
Yeah. Uh...

429
00:30:50.786 --> 00:30:52.019
what do you got for kids?

430
00:30:52.052 --> 00:30:53.952
Kids?

431
00:30:53.986 --> 00:30:56.886
You have something for a boy to read?

432
00:30:56.919 --> 00:30:59.086
How old is this boy?

433
00:30:59.119 --> 00:31:00.786
He's 10.

434
00:31:11.752 --> 00:31:13.019
Here you are.

435
00:31:14.919 --> 00:31:16.186
What's this?

436
00:31:16.219 --> 00:31:17.919
Adventures of Huckleberry Finn.

437
00:31:17.952 --> 00:31:19.119
I've never heard of it.

438
00:31:19.152 --> 00:31:20.186
He'll like it.

439
00:31:20.219 --> 00:31:22.786
- How much?
- 3 marks.

440
00:31:22.819 --> 00:31:25.752
Say. the. uh. gal who just came in here.

441
00:31:25.786 --> 00:31:26.986
what did she buy?

442
00:31:27.019 --> 00:31:28.819
What gal?

443
00:31:28.852 --> 00:31:29.986
The pretty one? You know?

444
00:31:30.019 --> 00:31:31.580
She was just in here a few minutes ago.

445
00:31:33.319 --> 00:31:35.552
I'm sorry. I don’t remember any gal.

446
00:31:39.952 --> 00:31:41.019
Well. thank you.

447
00:31:53.319 --> 00:31:56.619
"...when they shall be afraid
of that which is high.

448
00:31:56.652 --> 00:31:59.852
"and fears shall bein the way.

449
00:31:59.886 --> 00:32:02.752
"and the almond tree shall flourish.

450
00:32:02.786 --> 00:32:04.952
and the grasshopper shall be a burden..."

451
00:32:29.819 --> 00:32:31.552
Come on. Frank.

452
00:32:45.119 --> 00:32:48.219
Frank? Frank. it's me.

453
00:32:48.252 --> 00:32:50.052
Man: Is that Miss Crain?

454
00:33:42.886 --> 00:33:45.319
Ah. Mr. Baynes. good to see you again.

455
00:33:45.352 --> 00:33:46.752
Mr. Tagomi.

456
00:33:46.786 --> 00:33:48.052
- Please.
- Thanks.

457
00:33:53.886 --> 00:33:55.652
I see you’ve brought me something.

458
00:33:55.686 --> 00:33:57.819
Textile samples.

459
00:33:57.852 --> 00:34:00.219
Finest Swedish craftmanship.

460
00:34:00.252 --> 00:34:02.586
Oh!

461
00:34:02.619 --> 00:34:05.519
Our distributors will be delighted.

462
00:34:12.352 --> 00:34:15.319
I trust your visit has been
uneventful. Colonel Wegener.

463
00:34:15.352 --> 00:34:18.752
Until I received your call this afternoon.

464
00:34:18.786 --> 00:34:20.719
Is everything all right
with the Crown Prince?

465
00:34:20.752 --> 00:34:24.652
Yes. His ship will dock
tomorrow morning as scheduled.

466
00:34:24.686 --> 00:34:26.186
Then why have I been called?

467
00:34:26.219 --> 00:34:28.752
Your meeting must be canceled.

468
00:34:28.786 --> 00:34:30.052
Canceled?

469
00:34:30.086 --> 00:34:32.052
Ambassador Reiss came to see me today.

470
00:34:32.086 --> 00:34:34.152
along with an S.S.officer-- Diels.

471
00:34:34.186 --> 00:34:35.652
I know who he is.

472
00:34:35.686 --> 00:34:37.986
He reports directly to Heydrich in Berlin.

473
00:34:38.019 --> 00:34:39.886
They're determined to find a woman

474
00:34:39.919 --> 00:34:43.119
smuggling a film destined for
the Man In the High Castle.

475
00:34:43.152 --> 00:34:44.919
What does that have to do with us?

476
00:34:44.952 --> 00:34:47.152
We did not inform them about the smuggler.

477
00:34:47.186 --> 00:34:48.552
and yet they knew.

478
00:34:48.586 --> 00:34:50.252
It's clear your Nazi colleagues

479
00:34:50.286 --> 00:34:52.819
have infiltrated our security services.

480
00:34:52.852 --> 00:34:54.719
It's hardly a surprise.

481
00:34:54.752 --> 00:34:56.852
To this degree the risk is too great.

482
00:34:58.819 --> 00:35:00.552
Is that what your sticks tell you?

483
00:35:00.586 --> 00:35:03.319
Do you knowhow long I've worked

484
00:35:03.352 --> 00:35:04.919
to organize this meeting?

485
00:35:04.952 --> 00:35:06.852
The risk I've taken to come here?

486
00:35:06.886 --> 00:35:09.019
- I understand.
- I don't think you do.

487
00:35:09.052 --> 00:35:11.752
The Führer is ill. and he could die.

488
00:35:11.786 --> 00:35:13.719
and when he does.

489
00:35:13.752 --> 00:35:17.186
there will be a war between
our empires. Mr. Tagomi.

490
00:35:17.219 --> 00:35:19.619
There will be another time.

491
00:35:19.652 --> 00:35:22.019
I cannot travel twice on a
forged Swedish passport.

492
00:35:22.052 --> 00:35:23.186
I'll be shot.

493
00:35:23.219 --> 00:35:25.752
Give me the secrets.

494
00:35:25.786 --> 00:35:27.019
Let me deliver them.

495
00:35:28.252 --> 00:35:29.952
And if that oracle of yours

496
00:35:29.986 --> 00:35:32.752
tells you not to go through with it?

497
00:35:38.086 --> 00:35:40.786
You said it yourself. Mr. Tagomi.

498
00:35:40.819 --> 00:35:43.886
Destiny is in the hands of men.

499
00:35:43.919 --> 00:35:48.119
I'm afraid this time that means me.

500
00:36:11.086 --> 00:36:12.952
Mrs. Crothers. isn't it?

501
00:36:12.986 --> 00:36:13.986
Yes.

502
00:36:14.019 --> 00:36:15.119
I'm Chief Inspector Kido.

503
00:36:15.152 --> 00:36:16.552
Thank you for coming in.

504
00:36:18.886 --> 00:36:21.919
Well. we weren't given a choice. actually.

505
00:36:21.952 --> 00:36:23.986
We appreciate your cooperation.

506
00:36:24.019 --> 00:36:28.152
This must be John.

507
00:36:28.186 --> 00:36:29.752
And Emily.

508
00:36:32.152 --> 00:36:33.819
We'll need a picture. please.

509
00:36:40.819 --> 00:36:42.286
What's this about. Inspector?

510
00:36:42.319 --> 00:36:43.852
Oh. it's a formality.

511
00:36:43.886 --> 00:36:45.852
We're reviewing the
records of your brother.

512
00:36:45.886 --> 00:36:47.586
Frank? Is he okay?

513
00:36:47.619 --> 00:36:49.152
He's fine. Please.

514
00:36:49.186 --> 00:36:51.786
we have a very comfortable
waiting room down the hall.

515
00:36:51.819 --> 00:36:53.886
I'll be with you as soon as possible.

516
00:36:53.919 --> 00:36:55.719
How long will we be here?

517
00:36:55.752 --> 00:36:56.986
Not long.

518
00:36:57.019 --> 00:36:58.019
I hope.

519
00:36:58.052 --> 00:36:59.686
Please follow me.

520
00:37:27.219 --> 00:37:29.286
Mom. may we watch TV?

521
00:37:29.319 --> 00:37:31.852
Yes. Yes. of course.

522
00:37:31.886 --> 00:37:34.186
Please. make yourselves comfortable.

523
00:37:34.219 --> 00:37:36.152
Oh. Thank you.

524
00:38:05.152 --> 00:38:07.019
It's a beautiful family.

525
00:38:14.752 --> 00:38:16.986
W-What are you going to do?

526
00:38:17.019 --> 00:38:19.519
You've heard of Zyklon D?

527
00:38:24.319 --> 00:38:27.319
It's a gas. It's a gas.

528
00:38:27.352 --> 00:38:30.319
It is much improved since the war.

529
00:38:30.352 --> 00:38:34.119
Odorless and fast-acting.

530
00:38:36.152 --> 00:38:38.619
They'll fall asleep and never wake up.

531
00:38:43.919 --> 00:38:46.119
J-Just let them go.

532
00:38:50.586 --> 00:38:52.219
Where is Juliana Crain?

533
00:38:55.686 --> 00:38:59.152
We know Miss Walker met
her at an herb shop.

534
00:38:59.186 --> 00:39:03.019
We know she gave her the film.

535
00:39:03.052 --> 00:39:06.319
We even know she took
it to the Neutral Zone.

536
00:39:06.352 --> 00:39:09.652
We believe she was at the bus terminal.

537
00:39:09.686 --> 00:39:13.286
So all you need to tell us
is which bus she boarded.

538
00:39:15.986 --> 00:39:17.986
Where is Juliana Crain?

539
00:39:23.186 --> 00:39:25.719
Is it worth dying for her?

540
00:39:27.819 --> 00:39:29.886
A woman who thinks you are a failure?

541
00:39:31.186 --> 00:39:33.252
